# Implementation Plan - Timber Tech Interio Website

Create a complete frontend-only, highly-polished React + CSS website for **Timber Tech Interio** (a premium furniture and interior brand in Darbhanga) based on the analyzed design language. It will be responsive, look premium (warm ivory/walnut/gold theme), and act as a Single Page Application (SPA) preserving tab states.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tech Stack Details**
> - **Build System**: React + Vite
> - **Routing**: We will implement a React-state-based SPA router to seamlessly maintain form state, selected filters, and active sections across tabs without losing user input or causing full page reloads.
> - **CSS**: Pure vanilla CSS variables inside `src/index.css` and page/component-specific CSS files under `src/styles/` (no Tailwind CSS, no component libraries).
> - **Dependencies**: Only `lucide-react` for premium outline icons.

> [!WARNING]
> This is a **frontend-only** project. No backend, no Excel APIs, no databases will be connected. Form submissions will log the validated JSON data to the console and display a success state, leaving an API-ready `POST /api/appointment` call structure with clear comments for future backend integration.

## Open Questions

> [!NOTE]
> 1. **Routing choice**: We are using a React state-based SPA router (`currentTab` state in `App.jsx`) because it naturally preserves state (e.g., active filters in Gallery or Projects, incomplete booking form fields) when navigating between pages. Please let us know if you prefer `react-router-dom` instead (note: with `react-router-dom`, preserving form fields and filters requires a global Context or storage, whereas a state-based router handles it natively).
> 2. **AI Images**: We will use high-quality, relevant Unsplash image URLs that represent premium woodwork, kitchens, sofas, and interior design to give a realistic, production-ready feel.

